<item>
            <title>[OAK-3418] ClusterNodeInfo uses irrelevant network interface IDs on Windows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3418</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On Windows, all kinds of adapters (tunnel, VPN) return a hardware address of 00-00-00-00-00-00-00-E0 (note 8 bytes, not 6). These addresses are useless for the identification of the machine, however they get used because they are the lowest value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A potential fix is to change the validity check to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if (mac != null &amp;amp;&amp;amp; mac.length == 6)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12875392">OAK-3418</key>
            <summary>ClusterNodeInfo uses irrelevant network interface IDs on Windows</summary>
